---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import { isoDate, formatDate } from '../../lib/dates';
const entries = (await getCollection('groundtruth')).sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf());
---
<Base title="Ground Truth — Aswath Subramanian" description="Measuring climate superpollutants honestly.">
  <h1>Ground Truth</h1>
  <p class="lead">Measuring superpollutants honestly.</p>
  <p>Most of what we "know" about superpollutant emissions &mdash; nitrous oxide, methane, refrigerants &mdash; isn't measured. It's assumed: a single emission factor standing in for a number that swings with season, load, and weather. The gap between the tonne we claim and the tonne that's real is where abatement and carbon credits quietly fail. This is where I take that apart, one gas at a time.</p>

  <h2 class="kicker">Deep dives</h2>
  <ul class="bare" role="list">
    {entries.map((e) => (
      <li class="entry">
        <a href={`/ground-truth/${e.id}/`}>{e.data.title}</a>
        {e.data.status
          ? <span class="date">{e.data.status}</span>
          : <time class="date" datetime={isoDate(e.data.date)}>{formatDate(e.data.date)}</time>}
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>
</Base>
